method.name: emulation_cfm_network_group_config
method.description: This procedure will configure simulated MPs for CFM/Y.1731 protocol.

description.text: For create and modify -mode, handle should be its parent Ethernet node handle. For delete -mode, -handle should be its own handle i.e CFM Bridge node handle. This argument determines if individual interface, session or router handles are returned by the current command. This applies only to the command on which it is specified. Setting this to 0 means that only NGPF-specific protocol stack handles will be returned. This will significantly decrease the size of command results and speed up script execution. The default is 0, meaning only protocol stack handles will be returned.

choice.choiceText: A string where there is no Maintenance Domain Name.

This is a string the terminal substring of which is an RFC1035 DNS Name, and the remainder of which is a text string, following the syntax of a DNS Name, denoting the identity of a particular Maintenance Domain.
This is a combination of MAC address followed by 2 Octet Integer Value.
This is an IETF RFC 2579 DisplayString, with the exception that character codes 0-31 (decimal) are not used.
